{
  "doc_id": "41446",
  "text": "Phytochromes Phytochromes (Phy) are photoreceptors sensitive to red and far red light found in bacteria, cyanobacteria, fungi and plants. These photoactive proteins are responsible for several light-dependent functions such as growth, development, seed germination and flowering, as well as a wide spectrum of mechanisms regulated by circadian rhythms [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Although phytochromes consist of five identified members (PhyA-E), only PhyB has been extensively studied for optogenetic purposes [CITATION_3] .",
